<task>
	<title>Explaining the Ratio</title>

	<task>
		<statement>
			<p>Calculate the perimeter of a circle with radius 60 miles using the formula <m>P=2\pi r</m> where <m>P</m> is the perimeter and <m>r</m> is the radius.</p>
